[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":152},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F03\u002Fnodejs-500-error-debugging\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F03\u002Fnodejs-500-error-debugging\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F03\u002Fnodejs-500-error-debugging\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F03\u002Fnodejs-500-error-debugging\u002F":127,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F03\u002Fnodejs-500-error-debugging\u002F":136},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20190503\u002F2483499053\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":109,"date":110,"description":111,"extension":112,"lang":113,"meta":114,"navigation":115,"path":116,"readingMinutes":117,"seo":118,"standalone":119,"stem":120,"tags":121,"tldr":124,"updated":124,"url":125,"__hash__":126},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fnodejs-500-error-debugging.md","Node.js Returning Error Code 500","9024834553",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":103},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,34,37,40,45,57,68,73,76,81,87,92],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Strange thing happened while working with Node.js yesterday — AJAX worked fine the day before, then suddenly broke.\nToday I found out why. Note on how dumb the cause was.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"the-problem","The problem",[17,25,26],{},"No matter how I called this API via AJAX, it kept returning Error code 500.",[17,28,29],{},[30,31],"img",{"alt":32,"src":33},"Image","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FWrfMX1W.png",[17,35,36],{},"First I tried calling APIs with other methods, like POST — those all went through fine. Only PUT and DELETE returned 500, which ruled out the database side.",[17,38,39],{},"To narrow it down today, I used Postman to debug — to figure out if it's a frontend issue or a real backend issue. As soon as I hit it, the problem showed up...",[17,41,42],{},[30,43],{"alt":32,"src":44},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FimU05Wk.png",[17,46,47,48,52,53,56],{},"Turns out the error was ",[49,50,51],"code",{},"req.params is not a function"," — there's no ",[49,54,55],{},"params"," method.",[17,58,59,60,63,64,67],{},"I'd typed an extra ",[49,61,62],{},"s"," by accident, so I changed it back to ",[49,65,66],{},"req.param",".",[17,69,70],{},[30,71],{"alt":32,"src":72},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FnEX8QeI.png",[17,74,75],{},"Tried AJAX again — works now, but a different message popped up...",[17,77,78],{},[30,79],{"alt":32,"src":80},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FPsxcHCH.png",[17,82,83,84,67],{},"A Google search for that message turned up an official Express note: Express 4 uses a different way to get ",[49,85,86],{},"param",[17,88,89],{},[30,90],{"alt":32,"src":91},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FjLZrG8X.png",[17,93,94,95,98,99,102],{},"So change ",[49,96,97],{},"const id = req.param('id')"," to ",[49,100,101],{},"const id = req.params.id;"," and we're done.",{"title":104,"searchDepth":105,"depth":105,"links":106},"",2,[107,108],{"id":14,"depth":105,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":105,"text":23},"Nodejs","2019-05-03 09:06:26","Strange thing happened while working with Node.js yesterday — AJAX worked fine the day before, then suddenly broke. Today I found out why. Note on how dumb the cause was.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002Fnodejs-500-error-debugging","1",{"title":6,"description":111},false,"en\u002FNodejs\u002Fnodejs-500-error-debugging",[122,123],"Node.js","Troubleshooting",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F03\u002Fnodejs-500-error-debugging\u002F","BKGci29Mew_ouJGAOvWnbLGK-wnogdlMupfmuZa6U-8",{"newer":128,"older":132},{"url":129,"title":130,"date":131},"\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F03\u002Fhow-to-design-your-own-learning\u002F","How to Design Your Own Learning","2019-05-03 09:53:55",{"url":133,"title":134,"date":135},"\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F02\u002Fhow-much-are-you-willing-to-sacrifice\u002F","How Much Are You Willing to Sacrifice for What You Want?","2019-05-02 10:24:41",[137,142,147],{"url":138,"title":139,"date":140,"readingMinutes":141},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2026\u002F01\u002F13\u002Frun-multiple-commands-with-concurrently\u002F","Tired of Opening Multiple Terminals to Run Commands? Use Concurrently","2026-01-13 09:45:28","2",{"url":143,"title":144,"date":145,"readingMinutes":146},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2025\u002F03\u002F13\u002Fhexschool-ecommerce-api-complete-tutorial\u002F","Hexschool Capstone Class Study Group: Complete E-commerce API Tutorial","2025-03-13 09:13:26","9",{"url":148,"title":149,"date":150,"readingMinutes":151},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2024\u002F12\u002F25\u002Fpm2-process-manager-not-pm25\u002F","PM2 Is Process Manager, Not PM2.5","2024-12-25 10:31:33","5",1784020370697]